<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-31T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-31T05:00:00-05:00" n="854" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d854">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/174: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-31T19:00:00+09:00">January 31, 1935—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 31—6:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>21. Department’s 10, January 30, 6 p.m.<note n="72" xml:id="d854fn72">Not
                                printed.</note> Conversations progressing steadily but no concrete
                            results yet obtained. Japanese officials promise definite written reply
                            next week to memorandum recently submitted by foreign oil companies
                            containing their desiderata and it is hoped then to be able to report
                            specific results.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>